        public static <T> T firstOrNull​(Iterable<T> iterable)
        Returns the given iterable's first element or null if no element found. If the iterator created by the iterable implements Resource it will be closed in a finally block after the single item has been retrieved, or failed to be retrieved.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of elements in iterable.
        Parameters:
        iterable - the Iterable to get elements from.
        Returns:
        the first element in the iterable, or null if no element found.

      • singleOrNull

        public static <T> T singleOrNull​(Iterable<T> iterable)
        Returns the given iterable's single element or null if no element found. If there is more than one element in the iterable a NoSuchElementException will be thrown. If the iterator created by the iterable implements Resource it will be closed in a finally block after the single item has been retrieved, or failed to be retrieved.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of elements in iterable.
        Parameters:
        iterable - the Iterable to get elements from.
        Returns:
        the single element in iterable, or null if no element found.
        Throws:
        NoSuchElementException - if more than one element was found.

      • single

        public static <T> T single​(Iterable<T> iterable)
        Returns the given iterable's single element. If there are no elements or more than one element in the iterable a NoSuchElementException will be thrown. If the iterator created by the iterable implements Resource it will be closed in a finally block after the single item has been retrieved, or failed to be retrieved.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of elements in iterable.
        Parameters:
        iterable - the Iterable to get elements from.
        Returns:
        the single element in the iterable.
        Throws:
        NoSuchElementException - if there isn't exactly one element.

      • single

        public static <T> T single​(Iterable<T> iterable,
                           T itemIfNone)
        Returns the given iterable's single element or itemIfNone if no element found. If there is more than one element in the iterable a NoSuchElementException will be thrown. If the iterator created by the iterable implements Resource it will be closed in a finally block after the single item has been retrieved, or failed to be retrieved.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of elements in iterable.
        Parameters:
        iterable - the Iterable to get elements from.
        itemIfNone - item to use if none is found
        Returns:
        the single element in iterable, or null if no element found.
        Throws:
        NoSuchElementException - if more than one element was found.

        public static <T> Stream<T> stream​(Iterable<T> iterable)
        Create a stream from the given iterable.

        Note: returned stream needs to be closed via BaseStream.close() if the given iterable implements Resource.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of elements in the given iterable
        Parameters:
        iterable - the iterable to convert to stream
        Returns:
        stream over the iterable elements
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - when the given iterable is null

      • stream

        public static <T> Stream<T> stream​(Iterable<T> iterable,
                                   int characteristics)
        Create a stream from the given iterable with given characteristics.

        Note: returned stream needs to be closed via BaseStream.close() if the given iterable implements Resource.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of elements in the given iterable
        Parameters:
        iterable - the iterable to convert to stream
        characteristics - the logical OR of characteristics for the underlying Spliterator
        Returns:
        stream over the iterable elements
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - when the given iterable is null

      • safeForAll

        public static <T,​E extends Exception> void safeForAll​(ThrowingConsumer<T,​E> consumer,
                                                            Iterable<T> subjects)
                                                     throws E extends Exception
        Method for calling a lambda function on many objects when it is expected that the function might throw an exception. First exception will be thrown and subsequent will be suppressed. This method guarantees that all subjects will be consumed, unless Error happens.
        Type Parameters:
        E - the type of exception anticipated, inferred from the lambda
        Parameters:
        consumer - lambda function to call on each object passed
        subjects - Iterable of objects to call the function on
        Throws:
        E - if consumption fails with this exception
        E extends Exception
